{
  "texts": [
    "The other estimate uses adaptive optics observations from the VLT instruments MUSE and OASIS (Simon et al. 2024) and favors a mass of 8.7 × 10 9 M.",
    "However, when considering a different stellar mass profile in the inner region (and thus a different mass-to-light ratio), this method obtains a mass estimate of 5.5 × 10 9 M.",
    "These ∼5 × 10 9 M mass estimates are within 1.5σ of the 2017 EHT mass estimate.",
    "Arguably, there are significant systematic uncertainties in the non-horizon scale mass estimates of M 87 * that require continued investigation.",
    "It is worth noting that there is a significant counter-clockwise change in the position angle of the brighter region in the ringlike structure from 2017 to 2018 (∼30 •)."
  ]
}